This involves modeling concepts as cognitive programs using primitive cognitive functions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of this architecture in robotics, which suggests that it may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of images, which suggests that it may belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of heuristics, which suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the explainability of the output, which suggests that it may also belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
